  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: when you send transaction as a response to another user `/request` command, \"Send\" button should become disabled. Now it is still active and you can tap on it again.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\"Send\" button is disabled\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\"Send\" button is enabled\r\n![fgdfg](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42276027-dbad1a94-7f9a-11e8-924b-db87fa4ef6a4.png)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n*Preconditions:* User A and User B are contacts and have a chat;\r\n\r\n- as User A: in 1-1 chat with User B send `/request` \r\n- as User B: in 1-1 with User A tap on Send\r\n- as User B: sign transaction, click on Got it to get back to chat\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly 04/07/2019 (0.9.21 (6157) node a339d7e)\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n* TF session (01:00 - 01:30): https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8514788/sessions/4395442033/?accessToken=GkRByRS3cLWHeczenGNvkV5sPBU\r\n\r\n",
